==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-bitter.ogg|Audio (US)}}
===Etymology===
Old English ''bitter''
===Adjective===
'''bitter''', '''more bitter''', '''most bitter'''

# Having an [[acrid]] [[taste]] (usually from a [[base|basic]] substance)
#: ''The coffee was bitter.''
# [[harsh|Harsh]], [[piercing]] or [[stinging]]
#: ''A bitter wind blew from the north.''
#: '''1999:''' ''It was at the end of February, ... when the world was cold, and a bitter wind howled down the moors....'' &mdash; Neil Gaiman, ''Stardust'', pg. 31 (Perennial paperback edition)
# [[hateful|Hateful]] or [[hostile]]
#: ''They're bitter enemies.''
# [[cynical|Cynical]] and [[resentful]]
#: ''I've been bitter ever since that defeat.''

